This paper deals with the geometric properties of point sets in the plane, specifically the existence and size of convex holes. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also involves probabilistic analysis, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.PR (Probability), and the use of asymptotic notation implies that it could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of the expected value of a random variable, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
